name: Background Feature Description
value: I command the respect of those who share my faith. I can perform the religious ceremonies of my faith. My companions and I can expect free healing and care at an establishment of my faith, though I must provide any material components needed for spells. Those who share my religion will support me at a modest lifestyle.

name: Background_History
value: I was born into a family that worshipped Heseva, the goddess of magic. My parents named me Grak, the oldest of 4 kids. The order went from Me, my little sister Gura, my little brother Gara, and the youngest, my second little sister, Gramu. My whole family was green in color, while I was the only one that was born white, which they explained was a very rare case for Tortles. My parents then passed away when I was only a year old. Their stories included mostly about using magic to help others as clerics, fighting alongside spell casters like wizards and sorcerers, fighters and assassins. They had tons of adventures, and they would never stop, not even on their deathbeds. They entrusted me to take care of my family until they were able to fend off for themselves. My siblings and we all had different likes and dislikes, which made us each go our own way. I liked the idea of helping others, while also dabbling in the arcane power, so I chose to be a cleric that focused on the arcane. Gura was the smartest between us, so she liked the idea of pure magic for offense and defense, making her a wizard at heart. Gara, went on to be a fighter, as he had this thing for the sound a sword makes when it is slashed through the air. Lastly, Gramu was always the mischievous one and was always the one to disappear unnoticed, so she preferred being a rogue instead. We lived on the shore of Kelenvair mostly working in the harbor to make some money just to eat. At some point in time, my siblings went their own way when we were just 10 years old. I stayed in Kelenvair and began working in the temple of Heseva. Giving my goddess all the time I have. I despised living in the city all because I wanted to live the life my family did. Adventuring. I did like one thing about it, is that there were strangers that were amazed at my skin color, stating they have never saw anything like that. They would always take souvenirs of our meeting. Sometimes I would give them a dead white scale, sometimes have an artisan draw a painting of the stranger and I. I long the day where I would have an adventure with other people. Hopefully they wonâ€™t be evil people, or at least wonâ€™t leave me behind to rot and die alone. Until then, I shall continue serving my goddess and helping in any way possible. Eventually going up the ranks, I changed my name to Oogway, and I was called Master at some point to those who were my underlings. So my name is now Master Oogway.

field.value: The Temple of Heseva in Kelenvair

name: Bond
value:
I will do whatever is necessary to keep my temple safe.
My siblings, and hope of seeing them again soon.

name: Class Features
value:
Cleric (Arcana Domain), level 3:
â—† Spellcasting (Cleric 1, PHB 58) [3 cantrips known]
   I can cast prepared cleric cantrips/spells, using Wisdom as my spellcasting ability
   I can use a holy symbol as a spellcasting focus
   I can cast my prepared cleric spells as rituals if they have the ritual tag
â—† Arcane Initiate (Arcana Domain 1, SCAG 125)
   I gain proficiency with Arcana and two wizard cantrips that count as cleric cantrips
â—† Channel Divinity (Cleric 2, PHB 58) [1Ã— per short rest]
   I can channel divine energy to cause an effect; the save for this is my cleric spell DC
â—† Channel Divinity: Turn Undead (Cleric 2, PHB 59)
   As an action, all undead within 30 ft that can see/hear me must make a Wisdom save
   If an undead fails this save, it is turned for 1 minute or until it takes any damage
   Turned: move away, never within 30 ft of me, no reactions or actions other than Dash
   Turned: may Dodge instead of Dash when nowhere to move and unable to escape bonds
â—† Channel Divinity: Arcane Abjuration (Arcana Domain 2, SCAG 125)
   As an action, one celestial, elemental, fey, or fiend within 30 ft must make a Wis save
   If it fails and is able to see/hear me, it is turned for 1 min or until it takes damage
   Turned: move away, never within 30 ft of me, no reactions or actions other than Dash
   Turned: may Dodge instead of Dash when nowhere to move and unable to escape bonds
   If its CR is low enough and it is not on its home plane, it is banished for 1 min instead
   Banished: sent to home plane, reappearing where it was if the effect ends before 1 min

name: Personality Trait
value:
I long for adventure. Any chance I get, I will consider joining.
I am enthusiastic about going places, and i like helping people who need it.

name: Racial Traits
value:
Tortle (+2 Strength, +1 Wisdom)
Claws: I can use my claws to make unarmed strikes dealing 1d4 slashing damage.
Hold Breath: I can hold my breath for up to 1 hour at a time.
Natural Armor: I have a base AC of 17, but I can't add my Dex to it or wear armour.
Shell Defense: As an action, I can withdraw into my shell and gain +4 AC and adv. on Str and Con saves, but I count as prone, have speed 0, have disadv. on Dex saves, and can't take reactions. The only action I can take is a bonus action to emerge from the shell.
